        public ECSignature sign(byte[] data,
                        boolean enforceLowS,
                        boolean beDeterministic)
        Signs data using the ECPrivateKey resulting in an ECDSA signature.
        Parameters:
        data - The data to sign
        enforceLowS - If signature should enforce low values of signature part `S`, according to BIP-62
        beDeterministic - If signing should use randomness or be deterministic according to RFC6979.
        Returns:
        An ECDSA Signature.
